26 trait SymDenotations { this: Context =>
27   import SymDenotations._
28 
29   /** Factory method for SymDenotion creation. All creations
30    *  should be done via this method.
31    */
32   def SymDenotation(
33     symbol: Symbol,
34     owner: Symbol,
35     name: Name,
36     initFlags: FlagSet,
37     initInfo: Type,
38     initPrivateWithin: Symbol = NoSymbol)(implicit ctx: Context): SymDenotation = {
39     val result =
40       if (symbol.isClass)
41         if (initFlags is Package) new PackageClassDenotation(symbol, owner, name, initFlags, initInfo, initPrivateWithin, ctx.runId)
42         else new ClassDenotation(symbol, owner, name, initFlags, initInfo, initPrivateWithin, ctx.runId)
43       else new SymDenotation(symbol, owner, name, initFlags, initInfo, initPrivateWithin)
44     result.validFor = stablePeriod
45     result
46   }
47 
48   def stillValid(denot: SymDenotation): Boolean =
49     if (denot.is(ValidForever) || denot.isRefinementClass || denot.isImport) true
50     else {
51       val initial = denot.initial
52       val firstPhaseId = initial.validFor.firstPhaseId.max(ctx.typerPhase.id)
53       if ((initial ne denot) || ctx.phaseId != firstPhaseId) {
54         ctx.withPhase(firstPhaseId).stillValidInOwner(initial) ||
55          // Workaround #1895: A symbol might not be entered into an owner
56          // until the second phase where it exists
57          (denot.validFor.containsPhaseId(firstPhaseId + 1)) &&
58            ctx.withPhase(firstPhaseId + 1).stillValidInOwner(initial)
59       } else
60         stillValidInOwner(denot)
61     }
62 
63   private[SymDenotations] def stillValidInOwner(denot: SymDenotation): Boolean = try {
64     val owner = denot.owner.denot
65     stillValid(owner) && (
66       !owner.isClass
67       || owner.isRefinementClass
68       || owner.is(Scala2x)
69       || (owner.unforcedDecls.lookupAll(denot.name) contains denot.symbol)
70       || denot.isSelfSym
71       || denot.isLocalDummy)
72   } catch {
73     case ex: StaleSymbol => false
74   }
75 
76   /** Explain why symbol is invalid; used for debugging only */
77   def traceInvalid(denot: Denotation): Boolean = {
78     def show(d: Denotation) = s"$d#${d.symbol.id}"
79     def explain(msg: String) = {
80       println(s"${show(denot)} is invalid at ${this.period} because $msg")
81       false
82     }
83     denot match {
84       case denot: SymDenotation =>
85         def explainSym(msg: String) = explain(s"$msg\ndefined = ${denot.definedPeriodsString}")
86         if (denot.is(ValidForever) || denot.isRefinementClass) true
87         else {
88           implicit val ctx = this
89           val initial = denot.initial
90           if ((initial ne denot) || ctx.phaseId != initial.validFor.firstPhaseId) {
91             ctx.withPhase(initial.validFor.firstPhaseId).traceInvalid(initial)
92           } else try {
93             val owner = denot.owner.denot
94             if (!traceInvalid(owner)) explainSym("owner is invalid")
95             else if (!owner.isClass || owner.isRefinementClass || denot.isSelfSym) true
96             else if (owner.unforcedDecls.lookupAll(denot.name) contains denot.symbol) true
97             else explainSym(s"decls of ${show(owner)} are ${owner.unforcedDecls.lookupAll(denot.name).toList}, do not contain ${denot.symbol}")
98           } catch {
99             case ex: StaleSymbol => explainSym(s"$ex was thrown")
100           }
101       }
102       case _ =>
103         explain("denotation is not a SymDenotation")
104     }
105   }
106 
107   /** Configurable: Accept stale symbol with warning if in IDE */
108   def staleOK = Config.ignoreStaleInIDE && mode.is(Mode.Interactive)
109 
110   /** Possibly accept stale symbol with warning if in IDE */
111   def acceptStale(denot: SingleDenotation): Boolean =
112     staleOK && {
113       ctx.echo(denot.staleSymbolMsg)
114       true
115     }
116 }

120   /** A sym-denotation represents the contents of a definition
121    *  during a period.
122    */
123   class SymDenotation private[SymDenotations] (
124     symbol: Symbol,
125     final val maybeOwner: Symbol,
126     final val name: Name,
127     initFlags: FlagSet,
128     initInfo: Type,
129     initPrivateWithin: Symbol = NoSymbol) extends SingleDenotation(symbol) {
130 
131     //assert(symbol.id != 4940, name)
132 
133     override def hasUniqueSym: Boolean = exists
134 
135     /** Debug only
136     override def validFor_=(p: Period) = {
137       super.validFor_=(p)
138     }
139     */
140     if (Config.checkNoSkolemsInInfo) assertNoSkolems(initInfo)
141 
142     // ------ Getting and setting fields -----------------------------
143 
144     private[this] var myFlags: FlagSet = adaptFlags(initFlags)
145     private[this] var myInfo: Type = initInfo
146     private[this] var myPrivateWithin: Symbol = initPrivateWithin
147     private[this] var myAnnotations: List[Annotation] = Nil
148 
149     /** The owner of the symbol; overridden in NoDenotation */
150     def owner: Symbol = maybeOwner
151 
152     /** The flag set */
153     final def flags(implicit ctx: Context): FlagSet = { ensureCompleted(); myFlags }
154 
155     /** The flag set without forcing symbol completion.
156      *  Should be used only for printing.
157      */
158     private[dotc] final def flagsUNSAFE = myFlags
159 
160     /** Adapt flag set to this denotation's term or type nature */
161     private def adaptFlags(flags: FlagSet) = if (isType) flags.toTypeFlags else flags.toTermFlags
162 
163     /** Update the flag set */
164     final def flags_=(flags: FlagSet): Unit =
165       myFlags = adaptFlags(flags)
166 
167     /** Set given flags(s) of this denotation */
168     final def setFlag(flags: FlagSet): Unit = { myFlags |= flags }
169 
170     /** Unset given flags(s) of this denotation */
171     final def resetFlag(flags: FlagSet): Unit = { myFlags &~= flags }
172 
173     /** Set applicable flags from `flags` which is a subset of {NoInits, PureInterface} */
174     final def setNoInitsFlags(flags: FlagSet): Unit = {
175       val mask = if (myFlags.is(Trait)) NoInitsInterface else NoInits
176       setFlag(flags & mask)
177     }
178 
179     private def isCurrent(fs: FlagSet) =
180       fs <= (
181         if (myInfo.isInstanceOf[SymbolLoader]) FromStartFlags
182         else AfterLoadFlags)
183 
184     /** Has this denotation one of the flags in `fs` set? */
185     final def is(fs: FlagSet)(implicit ctx: Context) =
186       (if (isCurrent(fs)) myFlags else flags) is fs
187 
188     /** Has this denotation one of the flags in `fs` set, whereas none of the flags
189      *  in `butNot` are set?
190      */
191     final def is(fs: FlagSet, butNot: FlagSet)(implicit ctx: Context) =
192       (if (isCurrent(fs) && isCurrent(butNot)) myFlags else flags) is (fs, butNot)
193 
194     /** Has this denotation all of the flags in `fs` set? */
195     final def is(fs: FlagConjunction)(implicit ctx: Context) =
196       (if (isCurrent(fs)) myFlags else flags) is fs
197 
198     /** Has this denotation all of the flags in `fs` set, whereas none of the flags
199      *  in `butNot` are set?
200      */
201     final def is(fs: FlagConjunction, butNot: FlagSet)(implicit ctx: Context) =
202       (if (isCurrent(fs) && isCurrent(butNot)) myFlags else flags) is (fs, butNot)
203 
204     /** The type info.
205      *  The info is an instance of TypeType iff this is a type denotation
206      *  Uncompleted denotations set myInfo to a LazyType.
207      */
208     final def info(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
209       def completeInfo = {
210         completeFrom(myInfo.asInstanceOf[LazyType]); info
211       }
212       if (myInfo.isInstanceOf[LazyType]) completeInfo else myInfo
213     }
214 
215     /** The type info, or, if symbol is not yet completed, the completer */
216     final def infoOrCompleter = myInfo
217 
218     /** Optionally, the info if it is completed */
219     final def unforcedInfo: Option[Type] = myInfo match {
220       case myInfo: LazyType => None
221       case _ => Some(myInfo)
222     }
223 
224     private def completeFrom(completer: LazyType)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit =
225       if (Config.showCompletions) {
226         println(i"${"  " * indent}completing ${if (isType) "type" else "val"} $name")
227         indent += 1
228 
229         if (myFlags is Touched) throw CyclicReference(this)
230         myFlags |= Touched
231 
232         // completions.println(s"completing ${this.debugString}")
233         try completer.complete(this)(ctx.withPhase(validFor.firstPhaseId))
234         catch {
235           case ex: CyclicReference =>
236             println(s"error while completing ${this.debugString}")
237             throw ex
238         }
239         finally {
240           indent -= 1
241           println(i"${"  " * indent}completed $name in $owner")
242         }
243       }
244       else {
245         if (myFlags is Touched) throw CyclicReference(this)
246         myFlags |= Touched
247         completer.complete(this)(ctx.withPhase(validFor.firstPhaseId))
248       }
249 
250     protected[dotc] def info_=(tp: Type) = {
251       /* // DEBUG
252        def illegal: String = s"illegal type for $this: $tp"
253       if (this is Module) // make sure module invariants that allow moduleClass and sourceModule to work are kept.
254         tp match {
255           case tp: ClassInfo => assert(tp.selfInfo.isInstanceOf[TermRefBySym], illegal)
256           case tp: NamedType => assert(tp.isInstanceOf[TypeRefBySym], illegal)
257           case tp: ExprType => assert(tp.resultType.isInstanceOf[TypeRefBySym], illegal)
258           case _ =>
259         }
260         */
261       if (Config.checkNoSkolemsInInfo) assertNoSkolems(tp)
262       myInfo = tp
263     }
264 
265     /** The name, except
266      *   - if this is a module class, strip the module class suffix
267      *   - if this is a companion object with a clash-avoiding name, strip the
268      *     "avoid clash" suffix
269      */
270     def effectiveName(implicit ctx: Context) =
271       if (this is ModuleClass) name.stripModuleClassSuffix
272       else name.exclude(AvoidClashName)
273 
274     /** The privateWithin boundary, NoSymbol if no boundary is given.
275      */
276     final def privateWithin(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = { ensureCompleted(); myPrivateWithin }
277 
278     /** Set privateWithin. */
279     protected[dotc] final def privateWithin_=(sym: Symbol): Unit =
280       myPrivateWithin = sym
281 
282     /** The annotations of this denotation */
283     final def annotations(implicit ctx: Context): List[Annotation] = {
284       ensureCompleted(); myAnnotations
285     }
286 
287     /** Update the annotations of this denotation */
288     final def annotations_=(annots: List[Annotation]): Unit =
289       myAnnotations = annots
290 
291     /** Does this denotation have an annotation matching the given class symbol? */
292     final def hasAnnotation(cls: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context) =
293       dropOtherAnnotations(annotations, cls).nonEmpty
294 
295     /** Apply transform `f` to all annotations of this denotation */
296     final def transformAnnotations(f: Annotation => Annotation)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit =
297       annotations = annotations.mapConserve(f)
298 
299     /** Keep only those annotations that satisfy `p` */
300     final def filterAnnotations(p: Annotation => Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit =
301       annotations = annotations.filterConserve(p)
302 
303     /** Optionally, the annotation matching the given class symbol */
304     final def getAnnotation(cls: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Option[Annotation] =
305       dropOtherAnnotations(annotations, cls) match {
306         case annot :: _ => Some(annot)
307         case nil => None
308       }
309 
310     /** The same as getAnnotation, but without ensuring
311      *  that the symbol carrying the annotation is completed
312      */
313     final def unforcedAnnotation(cls: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Option[Annotation] =
314       dropOtherAnnotations(myAnnotations, cls) match {
315         case annot :: _ => Some(annot)
316         case nil => None
317       }
318 
319     /** Add given annotation to the annotations of this denotation */
320     final def addAnnotation(annot: Annotation): Unit =
321       annotations = annot :: myAnnotations
322 
323     /** Remove annotation with given class from this denotation */
324     final def removeAnnotation(cls: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit =
325       annotations = myAnnotations.filterNot(_ matches cls)
326 
327     /** Remove any annotations with same class as `annot`, and add `annot` */
328     final def updateAnnotation(annot: Annotation)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
329       removeAnnotation(annot.symbol)
330       addAnnotation(annot)
331     }
332 
333     /** Add all given annotations to this symbol */
334     final def addAnnotations(annots: TraversableOnce[Annotation])(implicit ctx: Context): Unit =
335       annots.foreach(addAnnotation)
336 
337     @tailrec
338     private def dropOtherAnnotations(anns: List[Annotation], cls: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): List[Annotation] = anns match {
339       case ann :: rest => if (ann matches cls) anns else dropOtherAnnotations(rest, cls)
340       case Nil => Nil
341     }
342 
343     /** The denotation is completed: info is not a lazy type and attributes have defined values */
344     final def isCompleted: Boolean = !myInfo.isInstanceOf[LazyType]
345 
346     /** The denotation is in train of being completed */
347     final def isCompleting: Boolean = (myFlags is Touched) && !isCompleted
348 
349     /** The completer of this denotation. @pre: Denotation is not yet completed */
350     final def completer: LazyType = myInfo.asInstanceOf[LazyType]
351 
352     /** Make sure this denotation is completed */
353     final def ensureCompleted()(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = info
354 
355     /** The symbols defined in this class or object.
356      *  Careful! This does not force the type, so is compilation order dependent.
357      *  This method should be used only in the following circumstances:
358      *
359      *  1. When accessing type parameters or type parameter accessors (both are entered before
360      *     completion).
361      *  2. When obtaining the current scope in order to enter, rename or delete something there.
362      *  3. When playing it safe in order not to raise CylicReferences, e.g. for printing things
363      *     or taking more efficient shortcuts (e.g. the stillValid test).
364      */
365     final def unforcedDecls(implicit ctx: Context): Scope = myInfo match {
366       case cinfo: LazyType =>
367         val knownDecls = cinfo.decls
368         if (knownDecls ne EmptyScope) knownDecls
369         else { completeFrom(cinfo); unforcedDecls } // complete-once
370       case _ => info.decls
371     }
372 
373     /** If this is a package class, the symbols entered in it
374      *  before it is completed. (this is needed to eagerly enter synthetic
375      *  aliases such as AnyRef into a package class without forcing it.
376      *  Right now, the only usage is for the AnyRef alias in Definitions.
377      */
378     final private[core] def currentPackageDecls(implicit ctx: Context): MutableScope = myInfo match {
379       case pinfo: SymbolLoaders # PackageLoader => pinfo.currentDecls
380       case _ => unforcedDecls.openForMutations
381     }
382 
383     // ------ Names ----------------------------------------------
384 
385     /** The expanded name of this denotation. */
386     final def expandedName(implicit ctx: Context) =
387       if (name.is(ExpandedName) || isConstructor) name
388       else name.expandedName(initial.owner)
389         // need to use initial owner to disambiguate, as multiple private symbols with the same name
390         // might have been moved from different origins into the same class
391 
392     /** The name with which the denoting symbol was created */
393     final def originalName(implicit ctx: Context) = initial.effectiveName
394 
395     /** The encoded full path name of this denotation, where outer names and inner names
396      *  are separated by `separator` strings as indicated by the given name kind.
397      *  Drops package objects. Represents each term in the owner chain by a simple `_$`.
398      */
399     def fullNameSeparated(kind: QualifiedNameKind)(implicit ctx: Context): Name =
400       maybeOwner.fullNameSeparated(kind, kind, name)
401 
402     /** The encoded full path name of this denotation (separated by `prefixKind`),
403      *  followed by the separator implied by `kind` and the given `name`.
404      *  Drops package objects. Represents each term in the owner chain by a simple `_$`.
405      */
406      def fullNameSeparated(prefixKind: QualifiedNameKind, kind: QualifiedNameKind, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Name =
407       if (symbol == NoSymbol || isEffectiveRoot || kind == FlatName && is(PackageClass))
408         name
409       else {
410         var filler = ""
411         var encl = symbol
412         while (!encl.isClass && !encl.isPackageObject) {
413           encl = encl.owner
414           filler += "_$"
415         }
416         var prefix = encl.fullNameSeparated(prefixKind)
417         if (kind.separator == "$")
418           // duplicate scalac's behavior: don't write a double '$$' for module class members.
419           prefix = prefix.exclude(ModuleClassName)
420         def qualify(n: SimpleName) =
421           kind(prefix.toTermName, if (filler.isEmpty) n else termName(filler + n))
422         val fn = name rewrite {
423           case name: SimpleName => qualify(name)
424           case name @ AnyQualifiedName(_, _) => qualify(name.mangled.toSimpleName)
425         }
426         if (name.isTypeName) fn.toTypeName else fn.toTermName
427       }
428 
429     /** The encoded flat name of this denotation, where joined names are separated by `separator` characters. */
430     def flatName(implicit ctx: Context): Name = fullNameSeparated(FlatName)
431 
432     /** `fullName` where `.' is the separator character */
433     def fullName(implicit ctx: Context): Name = fullNameSeparated(QualifiedName)

437     /** Is this denotation a type? */
438     override def isType: Boolean = name.isTypeName

440     /** Is this denotation a class? */
441     final def isClass: Boolean = isInstanceOf[ClassDenotation]
442

444     final def isRealClass(implicit ctx: Context) = isClass && !is(Trait)
445 
446     /** Cast to class denotation */
447     final def asClass: ClassDenotation = asInstanceOf[ClassDenotation]
448 
449     /** is this symbol the result of an erroneous definition? */
450     def isError: Boolean = false
451 
452     /** Make denotation not exist */
453     final def markAbsent(): Unit =
454       myInfo = NoType
455 
456     /** Is symbol known to not exist, or potentially not completed yet? */
457     final def unforcedIsAbsent(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
458       myInfo == NoType ||
459       (this is (ModuleVal, butNot = Package)) && moduleClass.unforcedIsAbsent
460 
461     /** Is symbol known to not exist? */
462     final def isAbsent(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = {
463       ensureCompleted()
464       myInfo == NoType ||
465       (this is (ModuleVal, butNot = Package)) && moduleClass.isAbsent
466     }
467 
468     /** Is this symbol the root class or its companion object? */
469     final def isRoot: Boolean =
470       (maybeOwner eq NoSymbol) && (name.toTermName == nme.ROOT || name == nme.ROOTPKG)
471 
472     /** Is this symbol the empty package class or its companion object? */
473     final def isEmptyPackage(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
474       name.toTermName == nme.EMPTY_PACKAGE && owner.isRoot
475 
476     /** Is this symbol the empty package class or its companion object? */
477     final def isEffectiveRoot(implicit ctx: Context) = isRoot || isEmptyPackage
478 
479     /** Is this symbol an anonymous class? */
480     final def isAnonymousClass(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
481       isClass && (initial.name startsWith str.ANON_CLASS)
482 
483     final def isAnonymousFunction(implicit ctx: Context) =
484       this.symbol.is(Method) && (initial.name startsWith str.ANON_FUN)
485 
486     final def isAnonymousModuleVal(implicit ctx: Context) =
487       this.symbol.is(ModuleVal) && (initial.name startsWith str.ANON_CLASS)
488 
489     /** Is this a companion class method or companion object method?
490      *  These methods are generated by Symbols#synthesizeCompanionMethod
491      *  and used in SymDenotations#companionClass and
492      *  SymDenotations#companionModule .
493      */
494     final def isCompanionMethod(implicit ctx: Context) =
495       name.toTermName == nme.COMPANION_CLASS_METHOD ||
496       name.toTermName == nme.COMPANION_MODULE_METHOD
497 
498     /** Is this a synthetic method that represents conversions between representations of a value class
499       *  These methods are generated in ExtensionMethods
500       *  and used in ElimErasedValueType.
501       */
502     final def isValueClassConvertMethod(implicit ctx: Context) =
503       name.toTermName == nme.U2EVT ||
504       name.toTermName == nme.EVT2U
505 
506     /** Is symbol a primitive value class? */
507     def isPrimitiveValueClass(implicit ctx: Context) =
508       maybeOwner == defn.ScalaPackageClass && defn.ScalaValueClasses().contains(symbol)
509 
510     /** Is symbol a primitive numeric value class? */
511     def isNumericValueClass(implicit ctx: Context) =
512       maybeOwner == defn.ScalaPackageClass && defn.ScalaNumericValueClasses().contains(symbol)
513 
514     /** Is symbol a class for which no runtime representation exists? */
515     def isNotRuntimeClass(implicit ctx: Context) = defn.NotRuntimeClasses contains symbol
516 
517     /** Is this symbol a class representing a refinement? These classes
518      *  are used only temporarily in Typer and Unpickler as an intermediate
519      *  step for creating Refinement types.
520      */
521     final def isRefinementClass(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
522       name == tpnme.REFINE_CLASS
523 
524     /** Is this symbol a package object or its module class? */
525     def isPackageObject(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = {
526       val nameMatches =
527         if (isType) name == tpnme.PACKAGE.moduleClassName
528         else name == nme.PACKAGE
529       nameMatches && (owner is Package) && (this is Module)
530     }
531 
532     /** Is this symbol an abstract type? */
533     final def isAbstractType(implicit ctx: Context) = this is DeferredType
534 
535     /** Is this symbol an alias type? */
536     final def isAliasType(implicit ctx: Context) = isAbstractOrAliasType && !(this is Deferred)
537 
538     /** Is this symbol an abstract or alias type? */
539     final def isAbstractOrAliasType = isType & !isClass
540 
541     /** Is this symbol an abstract type or type parameter? */
542     final def isAbstractOrParamType(implicit ctx: Context) = this is DeferredOrTypeParam
543 
544     /** Is this the denotation of a self symbol of some class?
545      *  This is the case if one of two conditions holds:
546      *  1. It is the symbol referred to in the selfInfo part of the ClassInfo
547      *     which is the type of this symbol's owner.
548      *  2. This symbol is owned by a class, it's selfInfo field refers to a type
549      *     (indicating the self definition does not introduce a name), and the
550      *     symbol's name is "_".
551      *  TODO: Find a more robust way to characterize self symbols, maybe by
552      *       spending a Flag on them?
553      */
554     final def isSelfSym(implicit ctx: Context) = owner.infoOrCompleter match {
555       case ClassInfo(_, _, _, _, selfInfo) =>
556         selfInfo == symbol ||
557           selfInfo.isInstanceOf[Type] && name == nme.WILDCARD
558       case _ => false
559     }
560 
561     /** Is this definition contained in `boundary`?
562      *  Same as `ownersIterator contains boundary` but more efficient.
563      */
564     final def isContainedIn(boundary: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = {
565       def recur(sym: Symbol): Boolean =
566         if (sym eq boundary) true
567         else if (sym eq NoSymbol) false
568         else if ((sym is PackageClass) && !(boundary is PackageClass)) false
569         else recur(sym.owner)
570       recur(symbol)
571     }
572 
573     final def isProperlyContainedIn(boundary: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
574       symbol != boundary && isContainedIn(boundary)
575 
576     /** Is this denotation static (i.e. with no outer instance)? */
577     final def isStatic(implicit ctx: Context) =
578       (if (maybeOwner eq NoSymbol) isRoot else maybeOwner.originDenotation.isStaticOwner) ||
579         myFlags.is(JavaStatic)
580 
581     /** Is this a package class or module class that defines static symbols? */
582     final def isStaticOwner(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
583       myFlags.is(ModuleClass) && (myFlags.is(PackageClass) || isStatic)
584 
585     /** Is this denotation defined in the same scope and compilation unit as that symbol? */
586     final def isCoDefinedWith(that: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context) =
587       (this.effectiveOwner == that.effectiveOwner) &&
588       (  !(this.effectiveOwner is PackageClass)
589         || this.unforcedIsAbsent || that.unforcedIsAbsent
590         || { // check if they are defined in the same file(or a jar)
591            val thisFile = this.symbol.associatedFile
592            val thatFile = that.symbol.associatedFile
593            (  thisFile == null
594            || thatFile == null
595            || thisFile.path == thatFile.path // Cheap possibly wrong check, then expensive normalization
596            || thisFile.canonicalPath == thatFile.canonicalPath
597            )
598          }
599       )
600 
601     /** Is this a denotation of a stable term (or an arbitrary type)? */
602     final def isStable(implicit ctx: Context) =
603       isType || is(Stable) || !(is(UnstableValue) || info.isInstanceOf[ExprType])
604 
605     /** Is this a "real" method? A real method is a method which is:
606      *  - not an accessor
607      *  - not a label
608      *  - not an anonymous function
609      *  - not a companion method
610      */
611     final def isRealMethod(implicit ctx: Context) =
612       this.is(Method, butNot = AccessorOrLabel) &&
613         !isAnonymousFunction &&
614         !isCompanionMethod
615 
616     /** Is this a getter? */
617     final def isGetter(implicit ctx: Context) =
618       (this is Accessor) && !originalName.isSetterName && !originalName.isScala2LocalSuffix
619 
620     /** Is this a setter? */
621     final def isSetter(implicit ctx: Context) =
622       (this is Accessor) &&
623       originalName.isSetterName &&
624       (!isCompleted || info.firstParamTypes.nonEmpty) // to avoid being fooled by   var x_= : Unit = ...
625 
626     /** is this a symbol representing an import? */
627     final def isImport = name == nme.IMPORT
628 
629     /** is this the constructor of a class? */
630     final def isClassConstructor = name == nme.CONSTRUCTOR
631 
632     /** Is this the constructor of a trait? */
633     final def isImplClassConstructor = name == nme.TRAIT_CONSTRUCTOR
634 
635     /** Is this the constructor of a trait or a class */
636     final def isConstructor = name.isConstructorName
637 
638     /** Is this a local template dummmy? */
639     final def isLocalDummy: Boolean = name.isLocalDummyName
640 
641     /** Does this symbol denote the primary constructor of its enclosing class? */
642     final def isPrimaryConstructor(implicit ctx: Context) =
643       isConstructor && owner.primaryConstructor == symbol
644 
645     /** Does this symbol denote the static constructor of its enclosing class? */
646     final def isStaticConstructor(implicit ctx: Context) =
647       name.isStaticConstructorName
648 
649     /** Is this a subclass of the given class `base`? */
650     def isSubClass(base: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context) = false
651 
652     /** Is this a subclass of `base`,
653      *  and is the denoting symbol also different from `Null` or `Nothing`?
654      *  @note  erroneous classes are assumed to derive from all other classes
655      *         and all classes derive from them.
656      */
657     def derivesFrom(base: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context) = false
658 
659     /** Is this symbol a class that extends `AnyVal`? */
660     final def isValueClass(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = {
661       val di = initial
662       di.isClass &&
663       di.derivesFrom(defn.AnyValClass)(ctx.withPhase(di.validFor.firstPhaseId))
664         // We call derivesFrom at the initial phase both because AnyVal does not exist
665         // after Erasure and to avoid cyclic references caused by forcing denotations
666     }
667 
668     /** Is this symbol a class references to which that are supertypes of null? */
669     final def isNullableClass(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
670       isClass && !isValueClass && !(this is ModuleClass) && symbol != defn.NothingClass && !defn.isPhantomTerminalClass(symbol)
671 
672     /** Is this definition accessible as a member of tree with type `pre`?
673      *  @param pre          The type of the tree from which the selection is made
674      *  @param superAccess  Access is via super
675      *  Everything is accessible if `pre` is `NoPrefix`.
676      *  A symbol with type `NoType` is not accessible for any other prefix.
677      */
678     final def isAccessibleFrom(pre: Type, superAccess: Boolean = false, whyNot: StringBuffer = null)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = {
679 
680       /** Are we inside definition of `boundary`? */
681       def accessWithin(boundary: Symbol) = ctx.owner.isContainedIn(boundary)
682 
683       /** Are we within definition of linked class of `boundary`? */
684       def accessWithinLinked(boundary: Symbol) = {
685         val linked = boundary.linkedClass
686         (linked ne NoSymbol) && accessWithin(linked)
687       }
688 
689       /** Is `pre` the same as C.thisThis, where C is exactly the owner of this symbol,
690        *  or, if this symbol is protected, a subclass of the owner?
691        */
692       def isCorrectThisType(pre: Type): Boolean = pre match {
693         case pre: ThisType =>
694           (pre.cls eq owner) || (this is Protected) && pre.cls.derivesFrom(owner)
695         case pre: TermRef =>
696           pre.symbol.moduleClass == owner
697         case _ =>
698           false
699       }
700 
701       /** Is protected access to target symbol permitted? */
702       def isProtectedAccessOK = {
703         def fail(str: => String): Boolean = {
704           if (whyNot != null) whyNot append str
705           false
706         }
707         val cls = owner.enclosingSubClass
708         if (!cls.exists)
709           fail(
710             i"""
711                | Access to protected $this not permitted because enclosing ${ctx.owner.enclosingClass.showLocated}
712                | is not a subclass of ${owner.showLocated} where target is defined""")
713         else if (
714           !(  isType // allow accesses to types from arbitrary subclasses fixes #4737
715            || pre.derivesFrom(cls)
716            || isConstructor
717            || (owner is ModuleClass) // don't perform this check for static members
718            ))
719           fail(
720             i"""
721                | Access to protected ${symbol.show} not permitted because prefix type ${pre.widen.show}
722                | does not conform to ${cls.showLocated} where the access takes place""")
723         else true
724       }
725 
726       if (pre eq NoPrefix) true
727       else if (info eq NoType) false
728       else {
729         val boundary = accessBoundary(owner)
730 
731         (  boundary.isTerm
732         || boundary.isRoot
733         || (accessWithin(boundary) || accessWithinLinked(boundary)) &&
734              (  !(this is Local)
735              || (owner is ImplClass) // allow private local accesses to impl class members
736              || isCorrectThisType(pre)
737              ) &&
738              (!(this.is(Private) && owner.is(Package)) ||
739               owner == ctx.owner.enclosingPackageClass)
740         || (this is Protected) &&
741              (  superAccess
742              || pre.isInstanceOf[ThisType]
743              || ctx.phase.erasedTypes
744              || isProtectedAccessOK
745              )
746         )
747       }
748     }
749 
750     /** Do members of this symbol need translation via asSeenFrom when
751      *  accessed via prefix `pre`?
752      */
753     def membersNeedAsSeenFrom(pre: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
754       !(  this.isTerm
755        || this.isStaticOwner
756        || ctx.erasedTypes
757        || (pre eq NoPrefix) || (pre eq thisType)
758        )
759 
760     /** Is this symbol concrete, or that symbol deferred? */
761     def isAsConcrete(that: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
762       !(this is Deferred) || (that is Deferred)
763 
764     /** Does this symbol have defined or inherited default parameters? */
765     def hasDefaultParams(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
766       if (this is HasDefaultParams) true
767       else if (this is NoDefaultParams) false
768       else {
769         val result = allOverriddenSymbols exists (_.hasDefaultParams)
770         setFlag(if (result) InheritedDefaultParams else NoDefaultParams)
771         result
772       }
773 
774     /** Symbol is an owner that would be skipped by effectiveOwner. Skipped are
775      *   - package objects
776      *   - labels
777      *   - non-lazy valdefs
778      */
779     def isWeakOwner(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
780       isPackageObject ||
781       isTerm && !is(MethodOrLazy, butNot = Label) && !isLocalDummy
782 
783     def isSkolem: Boolean = name == nme.SKOLEM
784 
785     def isInlineMethod(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = is(InlineMethod, butNot = Accessor)
786 
787     /** ()T and => T types should be treated as equivalent for this symbol.
788      *  Note: For the moment, we treat Scala-2 compiled symbols as loose matching,
789      *  because the Scala library does not always follow the right conventions.
790      *  Examples are: isWhole(), toInt(), toDouble() in BigDecimal, Numeric, RichInt, ScalaNumberProxy.
791      */
792     def matchNullaryLoosely(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = {
793       def test(sym: Symbol) =
794         sym.is(JavaDefined) ||
795         sym.owner == defn.AnyClass ||
796         sym == defn.Object_clone ||
797         sym.owner.is(Scala2x)
798       this.exists && (test(symbol) || allOverriddenSymbols.exists(test))
799     }
800 
801     // ------ access to related symbols ---------------------------------
802 
803     /* Modules and module classes are represented as follows:
804      *
805      * object X extends Y { def f() }
806      *
807      * <module> lazy val X: X$ = new X$
808      * <module> class X$ extends Y { this: X.type => def f() }
809      *
810      * During completion, references to moduleClass and sourceModules are stored in
811      * the completers.
812      */
813     /** The class implementing this module, NoSymbol if not applicable. */
814     final def moduleClass(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
815       def notFound = {
816       	if (Config.showCompletions) println(s"missing module class for $name: $myInfo")
817       	NoSymbol
818       }
819       if (this is ModuleVal)
820         myInfo match {
821           case info: TypeRef           => info.symbol
822           case ExprType(info: TypeRef) => info.symbol // needed after uncurry, when module terms might be accessor defs
823           case info: LazyType          => info.moduleClass
824           case t: MethodType           =>
825             t.resultType match {
826               case info: TypeRef => info.symbol
827               case _ => notFound
828             }
829           case _ => notFound
830         }
831       else NoSymbol
832     }
833 
834     /** The module implemented by this module class, NoSymbol if not applicable. */
835     final def sourceModule(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = myInfo match {
836       case ClassInfo(_, _, _, _, selfType) if this is ModuleClass =>
837         selfType match {
838           case selfType: TermRef => selfType.symbol
839           case selfType: Symbol => selfType.info.asInstanceOf[TermRef].symbol
840         }
841       case info: LazyType =>
842         info.sourceModule
843       case _ =>
844         NoSymbol
845     }
846 
847     /** The field accessed by this getter or setter, or if it does not exist, the getter */
848     def accessedFieldOrGetter(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
849       val fieldName = if (isSetter) name.asTermName.getterName else name
850       val d = owner.info.decl(fieldName)
851       val field = d.suchThat(!_.is(Method)).symbol
852       def getter = d.suchThat(_.info.isParameterless).symbol
853       field orElse getter
854     }
855 
856     /** The field accessed by a getter or setter, or
857      *  if it does not exists, the getter of a setter, or
858      *  if that does not exist the symbol itself.
859      */
860     def underlyingSymbol(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
861       if (is(Accessor)) accessedFieldOrGetter orElse symbol else symbol
862 
863     /** The chain of owners of this denotation, starting with the denoting symbol itself */
864     final def ownersIterator(implicit ctx: Context) = new Iterator[Symbol] {
865       private[this] var current = symbol
866       def hasNext = current.exists
867       def next: Symbol = {
868         val result = current
869         current = current.owner
870         result
871       }
872     }
873 
874     /** If this is a weak owner, its owner, otherwise the denoting symbol. */
875     final def skipWeakOwner(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
876       if (isWeakOwner) owner.skipWeakOwner else symbol
877 
878     /** The owner, skipping package objects, labels and non-lazy valdefs. */
879     final def effectiveOwner(implicit ctx: Context) = owner.skipWeakOwner
880 
881     /** The class containing this denotation.
882      *  If this denotation is already a class, return itself
883      *  Definitions flagged with JavaStatic are treated specially.
884      *  Their enclosing class is not the lexically enclosing class,
885      *  but in turn the enclosing class of the latter. This reflects
886      *  the context created by `Context#superCallContext`, `Context#thisCallArgContext`
887      *  for these definitions.
888      *
889      *  Note, that as packages have ClassSymbols, top level classes will have an `enclosingClass`
890      *  with Package flag set.
891      */
892     final def enclosingClass(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
893       def enclClass(sym: Symbol, skip: Boolean): Symbol = {
894         def newSkip = sym.is(JavaStaticTerm)
895         if (!sym.exists)
896           NoSymbol
897         else if (sym.isClass)
898           if (skip) enclClass(sym.owner, newSkip) else sym
899         else
900           enclClass(sym.owner, skip || newSkip)
901       }
902       enclClass(symbol, false)
903     }
904 
905     /** A class that in source code would be lexically enclosing */
906     final def lexicallyEnclosingClass(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
907       if (!exists || isClass) symbol else owner.lexicallyEnclosingClass
908 
909     /** A symbol is effectively final if it cannot be overridden in a subclass */
910     final def isEffectivelyFinal(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
911       is(PrivateOrFinalOrInline) || !owner.isClass || owner.is(ModuleOrFinal) || owner.isAnonymousClass
912 
913     /** The class containing this denotation which has the given effective name. */
914     final def enclosingClassNamed(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
915       val cls = enclosingClass
916       if (cls.effectiveName == name || !cls.exists) cls else cls.owner.enclosingClassNamed(name)
917     }
918 
919     /** The closest enclosing method containing this definition.
920      *  A local dummy owner is mapped to the primary constructor of the class.
921      */
922     final def enclosingMethod(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
923       if (this is (Method, butNot = Label)) symbol
924       else if (this.isClass) primaryConstructor
925       else if (this.exists) owner.enclosingMethod
926       else NoSymbol
927 
928     /** The top-level class containing this denotation,
929      *  except for a toplevel module, where its module class is returned.
930      */
931     final def topLevelClass(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
932 
933       def topLevel(d: SymDenotation): Symbol =
934         if (!exists || d.isEffectiveRoot || (d is PackageClass) || (d.owner is PackageClass))
935           d.symbol
936         else
937           topLevel(d.owner)
938 
939       val sym = topLevel(this)
940       if (sym.isClass) sym else sym.moduleClass
941     }
942 
943     /** The package class containing this denotation */
944     final def enclosingPackageClass(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
945       if (this is PackageClass) symbol else owner.enclosingPackageClass
946 
947     /** The module object with the same (term-) name as this class or module class,
948      *  and which is also defined in the same scope and compilation unit.
949      *  NoSymbol if this module does not exist.
950      */
951     final def companionModule(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
952       if (this.flagsUNSAFE is Flags.Module) this.sourceModule
953       else {
954         val companionMethod = info.decls.denotsNamed(nme.COMPANION_MODULE_METHOD, selectPrivate).first
955         if (companionMethod.exists)
956           companionMethod.info.resultType.classSymbol.sourceModule
957         else
958           NoSymbol
959       }
960     }
961 
962 
963     /** The class with the same (type-) name as this module or module class,
964       *  and which is also defined in the same scope and compilation unit.
965       *  NoSymbol if this class does not exist.
966       */
967     final def companionClass(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
968       if (is(Package)) NoSymbol
969       else {
970         val companionMethod = info.decls.denotsNamed(nme.COMPANION_CLASS_METHOD, selectPrivate).first
971         if (companionMethod.exists)
972           companionMethod.info.resultType.classSymbol
973         else
974           NoSymbol
975       }
976 
977     final def scalacLinkedClass(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
978       if (this is ModuleClass) companionNamed(effectiveName.toTypeName)
979       else if (this.isClass) companionNamed(effectiveName.moduleClassName).sourceModule.moduleClass
980       else NoSymbol
981 
982     /** Find companion class symbol with given name, or NoSymbol if none exists.
983      *  Three alternative strategies:
984      *  1. If owner is a class, look in its members, otherwise
985      *  2. If current compilation unit has a typed tree,
986      *     determine the defining statement sequence and search its trees, otherwise
987      *  3. If context has an enclosing scope which defines this symbol,
988      *     lookup its companion in the same scope.
989      */
990     private def companionNamed(name: TypeName)(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
991       if (owner.isClass)
992         owner.info.decl(name).suchThat(_.isCoDefinedWith(symbol)).symbol
993       else if (!owner.exists || ctx.compilationUnit == null)
994         NoSymbol
995       else if (!ctx.compilationUnit.tpdTree.isEmpty)
996         tpd.definingStats(symbol).iterator
997           .map(tpd.definedSym)
998           .find(_.name == name)
999           .getOrElse(NoSymbol)
1000       else if (ctx.scope == null)
1001         NoSymbol
1002       else if (ctx.scope.lookup(this.name) == symbol)
1003         ctx.scope.lookup(name)
1004       else
1005         companionNamed(name)(ctx.outersIterator.dropWhile(_.scope eq ctx.scope).next())
1006 
1007     /** Is this symbol the same or a linked class of `sym`? */
1008     final def isLinkedWith(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
1009       (symbol eq sym) || (linkedClass eq sym)
1010 
1011     /** If this is a class, the module class of its companion object.
1012      *  If this is a module class, its companion class.
1013      *  NoSymbol otherwise.
1014      */
1015     final def linkedClass(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
1016       if (this is ModuleClass) companionClass
1017       else if (this.isClass) companionModule.moduleClass
1018       else NoSymbol
1019 
1020     /** The class that encloses the owner of the current context
1021      *  and that is a subclass of this class. NoSymbol if no such class exists.
1022      */
1023     final def enclosingSubClass(implicit ctx: Context) =
1024       ctx.owner.ownersIterator.findSymbol(_.isSubClass(symbol))
1025 
1026     /** The non-private symbol whose name and type matches the type of this symbol
1027      *  in the given class.
1028      *  @param inClass   The class containing the result symbol's definition
1029      *  @param site      The base type from which member types are computed
1030      *
1031      *  inClass <-- find denot.symbol      class C { <-- symbol is here
1032      *
1033      *                   site: Subtype of both inClass and C
1034      */
1035     final def matchingDecl(inClass: Symbol, site: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
1036       var denot = inClass.info.nonPrivateDecl(name)
1037       if (denot.isTerm) // types of the same name always match
1038         denot = denot.matchingDenotation(site, site.memberInfo(symbol))
1039       denot.symbol
1040     }
1041 
1042     /** The non-private member of `site` whose name and type matches the type of this symbol
1043      */
1044     final def matchingMember(site: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
1045       var denot = site.nonPrivateMember(name)
1046       if (denot.isTerm) // types of the same name always match
1047         denot = denot.matchingDenotation(site, site.memberInfo(symbol))
1048       denot.symbol
1049     }
1050 
1051     /** If false, this symbol cannot possibly participate in an override,
1052      *  either as overrider or overridee.
1053      */
1054     final def canMatchInheritedSymbols(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
1055       maybeOwner.isClass && memberCanMatchInheritedSymbols
1056 
1057     /** If false, this class member cannot possibly participate in an override,
1058      *  either as overrider or overridee.
1059      */
1060     final def memberCanMatchInheritedSymbols(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
1061       !isConstructor && !is(Private)
1062 
1063     /** The symbol, in class `inClass`, that is overridden by this denotation. */
1064     final def overriddenSymbol(inClass: ClassSymbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
1065       if (!canMatchInheritedSymbols && (owner ne inClass)) NoSymbol
1066       else matchingDecl(inClass, owner.thisType)
1067 
1068     /** All symbols overriden by this denotation. */
1069     final def allOverriddenSymbols(implicit ctx: Context): Iterator[Symbol] =
1070       if (!canMatchInheritedSymbols) Iterator.empty
1071       else overriddenFromType(owner.info)
1072 
1073     /** Returns all matching symbols defined in parents of the selftype. */
1074     final def extendedOverriddenSymbols(implicit ctx: Context): Iterator[Symbol] =
1075       if (!canMatchInheritedSymbols) Iterator.empty
1076       else overriddenFromType(owner.asClass.classInfo.selfType)
1077 
1078     private def overriddenFromType(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Iterator[Symbol] =
1079       tp.baseClasses match {
1080         case _ :: inherited => inherited.iterator map overriddenSymbol filter (_.exists)
1081         case Nil => Iterator.empty
1082       }
1083 
1084     /** The symbol overriding this symbol in given subclass `ofclazz`.
1085      *
1086      *  @param ofclazz is a subclass of this symbol's owner
1087      */
1088     final def overridingSymbol(inClass: ClassSymbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
1089       if (canMatchInheritedSymbols) matchingDecl(inClass, inClass.thisType)
1090       else NoSymbol
1091 
1092     /** The symbol accessed by a super in the definition of this symbol when
1093      *  seen from class `base`. This symbol is always concrete.
1094      *  pre: `this.owner` is in the base class sequence of `base`.
1095      */
1096     final def superSymbolIn(base: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
1097       @tailrec def loop(bcs: List[ClassSymbol]): Symbol = bcs match {
1098         case bc :: bcs1 =>
1099           val sym = matchingDecl(bcs.head, base.thisType)
1100             .suchThat(alt => !(alt is Deferred)).symbol
1101           if (sym.exists) sym else loop(bcs.tail)
1102         case _ =>
1103           NoSymbol
1104       }
1105       loop(base.info.baseClasses.dropWhile(owner != _).tail)
1106     }
1107 
1108     /** A member of class `base` is incomplete if
1109      *  (1) it is declared deferred or
1110      *  (2) it is abstract override and its super symbol in `base` is
1111      *      nonexistent or incomplete.
1112      */
1113     @tailrec final def isIncompleteIn(base: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
1114       (this is Deferred) ||
1115       (this is AbsOverride) && {
1116         val supersym = superSymbolIn(base)
1117         supersym == NoSymbol || supersym.isIncompleteIn(base)
1118       }
1119 
1120     /** The class or term symbol up to which this symbol is accessible,
1121      *  or RootClass if it is public.  As java protected statics are
1122      *  otherwise completely inaccessible in scala, they are treated
1123      *  as public.
1124      *  @param base  The access boundary to assume if this symbol is protected
1125      */
1126     final def accessBoundary(base: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
1127       val fs = flags
1128       if (fs is Private) owner
1129       else if (fs is StaticProtected) defn.RootClass
1130       else if (privateWithin.exists && !ctx.phase.erasedTypes) privateWithin
1131       else if (fs is Protected) base
1132       else defn.RootClass
1133     }
1134 
1135     /** The primary constructor of a class or trait, NoSymbol if not applicable. */
1136     def primaryConstructor(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = NoSymbol
1137 
1138     // ----- type-related ------------------------------------------------
1139 
1140     /** The type parameters of a class symbol, Nil for all other symbols */
1141     def typeParams(implicit ctx: Context): List[TypeSymbol] = Nil
1142 
1143     /** The type This(cls), where cls is this class, NoPrefix for all other symbols */
1144     def thisType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = NoPrefix
1145 
1146     override def typeRef(implicit ctx: Context): TypeRef =
1147       TypeRef(owner.thisType, symbol)
1148 
1149     override def termRef(implicit ctx: Context): TermRef =
1150       TermRef(owner.thisType, symbol)
1151 
1152     /** The variance of this type parameter or type member as an Int, with
1153      *  +1 = Covariant, -1 = Contravariant, 0 = Nonvariant, or not a type parameter
1154      */
1155     final def variance(implicit ctx: Context): Int =
1156       if (this is Covariant) 1
1157       else if (this is Contravariant) -1
1158       else 0
1159 
1160     /** The flags to be used for a type parameter owned by this symbol.
1161      *  Overridden by ClassDenotation.
1162      */
1163     def typeParamCreationFlags: FlagSet = TypeParam
1164 
1165     override def toString = {
1166       val kindString =
1167         if (myFlags is ModuleClass) "module class"
1168         else if (isClass) "class"
1169         else if (isType) "type"
1170         else if (myFlags is Module) "module"
1171         else if (myFlags is Method) "method"
1172         else "val"
1173       s"$kindString $name"
1174     }
1175 
1176     // ----- Sanity checks and debugging */
1177 
1178     def debugString = toString + "#" + symbol.id // !!! DEBUG
1179 
1180     def hasSkolems(tp: Type): Boolean = tp match {
1181       case tp: SkolemType => true
1182       case tp: NamedType => hasSkolems(tp.prefix)
1183       case tp: RefinedType => hasSkolems(tp.parent) || hasSkolems(tp.refinedInfo)
1184       case tp: RecType => hasSkolems(tp.parent)
1185       case tp: TypeBounds => hasSkolems(tp.lo) || hasSkolems(tp.hi)
1186       case tp: TypeVar => hasSkolems(tp.inst)
1187       case tp: ExprType => hasSkolems(tp.resType)
1188       case tp: AppliedType => hasSkolems(tp.tycon) || tp.args.exists(hasSkolems)
1189       case tp: LambdaType => tp.paramInfos.exists(hasSkolems) || hasSkolems(tp.resType)
1190       case tp: AndOrType => hasSkolems(tp.tp1) || hasSkolems(tp.tp2)
1191       case tp: AnnotatedType => hasSkolems(tp.tpe)
1192       case _ => false
1193     }
1194 
1195     def assertNoSkolems(tp: Type) =
1196       if (!this.isSkolem)
1197         assert(!hasSkolems(tp), s"assigning type $tp containing skolems to $this")
1198 
1199     // ----- copies and transforms  ----------------------------------------
1200 
1201     protected def newLikeThis(s: Symbol, i: Type): SingleDenotation = new UniqueRefDenotation(s, i, validFor)
1202 
1203     /** Copy this denotation, overriding selective fields */
1204     final def copySymDenotation(
1205       symbol: Symbol = this.symbol,
1206       owner: Symbol = this.owner,
1207       name: Name = this.name,
1208       initFlags: FlagSet = UndefinedFlags,
1209       info: Type = null,
1210       privateWithin: Symbol = null,
1211       annotations: List[Annotation] = null)(implicit ctx: Context) =
1212     { // simulate default parameters, while also passing implicit context ctx to the default values
1213       val initFlags1 = (if (initFlags != UndefinedFlags) initFlags else this.flags)
1214       val info1 = if (info != null) info else this.info
1215       if (ctx.isAfterTyper && changedClassParents(info, info1, completersMatter = false))
1216         assert(ctx.phase.changesParents, i"undeclared parent change at ${ctx.phase} for $this, was: $info, now: $info1")
1217       val privateWithin1 = if (privateWithin != null) privateWithin else this.privateWithin
1218       val annotations1 = if (annotations != null) annotations else this.annotations
1219       val d = ctx.SymDenotation(symbol, owner, name, initFlags1, info1, privateWithin1)
1220       d.annotations = annotations1
1221       d
1222     }
1223 
1224     /** Copy mamberNames and baseData caches from given denotation, provided
1225      *  they are valid at given `phase`.
1226      */
1227     def copyCaches(from: SymDenotation, phase: Phase)(implicit ctx: Context): this.type = this
1228 
1229     /** Are `info1` and `info2` ClassInfo types with different parents?
1230      *  @param completersMatter  if `true`, consider parents changed if `info1` or `info2 `is a type completer
1231      */
1232     protected def changedClassParents(info1: Type, info2: Type, completersMatter: Boolean): Boolean =
1233       info2 match {
1234         case info2: ClassInfo =>
1235           info1 match {
1236             case info1: ClassInfo => info1.classParents ne info2.classParents
1237             case _ => completersMatter
1238           }
1239         case _ => completersMatter
1240       }
1241 
1242     override def initial: SymDenotation = super.initial.asSymDenotation
1243 
1244     /** Install this denotation as the result of the given denotation transformer. */
1245     override def installAfter(phase: DenotTransformer)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit =
1246       super.installAfter(phase)
1247 
1248     /** Apply a transformation `f` to all denotations in this group that start at or after
1249      *  given phase. Denotations are replaced while keeping the same validity periods.
1250      */
1251     override def transformAfter(phase: DenotTransformer, f: SymDenotation => SymDenotation)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit =
1252       super.transformAfter(phase, f)
1253 
1254     /** If denotation is private, remove the Private flag and expand the name if necessary */
1255     def ensureNotPrivate(implicit ctx: Context) =
1256       if (is(Private))
1257         copySymDenotation(name = expandedName, initFlags = this.flags &~ Private)
1258       else this
1259   }
