1261   /** The contents of a class definition during a period
1262    */
1263   class ClassDenotation private[SymDenotations] (
1264     symbol: Symbol,
1265     maybeOwner: Symbol,
1266     name: Name,
1267     initFlags: FlagSet,
1268     initInfo: Type,
1269     initPrivateWithin: Symbol,
1270     initRunId: RunId)
1271     extends SymDenotation(symbol, maybeOwner, name, initFlags, initInfo, initPrivateWithin) {
1272 
1273     import util.LRUCache
1274 
1275     // ----- caches -------------------------------------------------------
1276 
1277     private[this] var myTypeParams: List[TypeSymbol] = null
1278     private[this] var fullNameCache: SimpleIdentityMap[QualifiedNameKind, Name] = SimpleIdentityMap.Empty
1279 
1280     private[this] var myMemberCache: LRUCache[Name, PreDenotation] = null
1281     private[this] var myMemberCachePeriod: Period = Nowhere
1282 
1283     /** A cache from types T to baseType(T, C) */
1284     type BaseTypeMap = java.util.HashMap[CachedType, Type]
1285     private[this] var myBaseTypeCache: BaseTypeMap = null
1286     private[this] var myBaseTypeCachePeriod: Period = Nowhere
1287 
1288     private var baseDataCache: BaseData = BaseData.None
1289     private var memberNamesCache: MemberNames = MemberNames.None
1290 
1291     private def memberCache(implicit ctx: Context): LRUCache[Name, PreDenotation] = {
1292       if (myMemberCachePeriod != ctx.period) {
1293         myMemberCache = new LRUCache
1294         myMemberCachePeriod = ctx.period
1295       }
1296       myMemberCache
1297     }
1298 
1299     private def baseTypeCache(implicit ctx: Context): BaseTypeMap = {
1300       if (!ctx.hasSameBaseTypesAs(myBaseTypeCachePeriod)) {
1301         myBaseTypeCache = new BaseTypeMap
1302         myBaseTypeCachePeriod = ctx.period
1303       }
1304       myBaseTypeCache
1305     }
1306 
1307     private def invalidateBaseDataCache() = {
1308       baseDataCache.invalidate()
1309       baseDataCache = BaseData.None
1310     }
1311 
1312     private def invalidateMemberNamesCache() = {
1313       memberNamesCache.invalidate()
1314       memberNamesCache = MemberNames.None
1315     }
1316 
1317     def invalidateBaseTypeCache() = {
1318       myBaseTypeCache = null
1319       myBaseTypeCachePeriod = Nowhere
1320     }
1321 
1322     override def copyCaches(from: SymDenotation, phase: Phase)(implicit ctx: Context): this.type = {
1323       from match {
1324         case from: ClassDenotation =>
1325           if (from.memberNamesCache.isValidAt(phase)) memberNamesCache = from.memberNamesCache
1326           if (from.baseDataCache.isValidAt(phase)) {
1327             baseDataCache = from.baseDataCache
1328             myBaseTypeCache = from.baseTypeCache
1329           }
1330         case _ =>
1331       }
1332       this
1333     }
1334 
1335     // ----- denotation fields and accessors ------------------------------
1336 
1337     if (initFlags is (Module, butNot = Package))
1338       assert(name.is(ModuleClassName), s"module naming inconsistency: ${name.debugString}")
1339 
1340     /** The symbol asserted to have type ClassSymbol */
1341     def classSymbol: ClassSymbol = symbol.asInstanceOf[ClassSymbol]
1342 
1343     /** The info asserted to have type ClassInfo */
1344     def classInfo(implicit ctx: Context): ClassInfo = info.asInstanceOf[ClassInfo]
1345 
1346     /** The type parameters in this class, in the order they appear in the current
1347      *  scope `decls`. This might be temporarily the incorrect order when
1348      *  reading Scala2 pickled info. The problem is fixed by `ensureTypeParamsInCorrectOrder`,
1349      *  which is called once an unpickled symbol has been completed.
1350      */
1351     private def typeParamsFromDecls(implicit ctx: Context) =
1352       unforcedDecls.filter(sym =>
1353         (sym is TypeParam) && sym.owner == symbol).asInstanceOf[List[TypeSymbol]]
1354 
1355     /** The type parameters of this class */
1356     override final def typeParams(implicit ctx: Context): List[TypeSymbol] = {
1357       if (myTypeParams == null)
1358         myTypeParams =
1359           if (ctx.erasedTypes || is(Module)) Nil // fast return for modules to avoid scanning package decls
1360           else {
1361             val di = initial
1362             if (this ne di) di.typeParams
1363             else infoOrCompleter match {
1364               case info: TypeParamsCompleter => info.completerTypeParams(symbol)
1365               case _ => typeParamsFromDecls
1366             }
1367           }
1368       myTypeParams
1369     }
1370 
1371     override protected[dotc] final def info_=(tp: Type) = {
1372       if (changedClassParents(infoOrCompleter, tp, completersMatter = true))
1373         invalidateBaseDataCache()
1374       invalidateMemberNamesCache()
1375       myTypeParams = null // changing the info might change decls, and with it typeParams
1376       super.info_=(tp)
1377     }
1378 
1379     def classParents(implicit ctx: Context): List[Type] = info match {
1380       case classInfo: ClassInfo => classInfo.parents
1381       case _ => Nil
1382     }
1383 
1384     /** The symbol of the superclass, NoSymbol if no superclass exists */
1385     def superClass(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = classParents match {
1386       case parent :: _ =>
1387         val cls = parent.classSymbol
1388         if (cls is Trait) NoSymbol else cls
1389       case _ =>
1390         NoSymbol
1391     }
1392 
1393     /** The explicitly given self type (self types of modules are assumed to be
1394      *  explcitly given here).
1395      */
1396     def givenSelfType(implicit ctx: Context) = classInfo.selfInfo match {
1397       case tp: Type => tp
1398       case self: Symbol => self.info
1399     }
1400 
1401    // ------ class-specific operations -----------------------------------
1402 
1403     private[this] var myThisType: Type = null
1404 
1405     /** The this-type depends on the kind of class:
1406      *  - for a package class `p`:  ThisType(TypeRef(Noprefix, p))
1407      *  - for a module class `m`: A term ref to m's source module.
1408      *  - for all other classes `c` with owner `o`: ThisType(TypeRef(o.thisType, c))
1409      */
1410     override def thisType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
1411       if (myThisType == null) myThisType = computeThisType
1412       myThisType
1413     }
1414 
1415     private def computeThisType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
1416       val cls = symbol.asType
1417       val pre = if (this is Package) NoPrefix else owner.thisType
1418       ThisType.raw(TypeRef(pre, cls))
1419     }
1420 
1421     private[this] var myTypeRef: TypeRef = null
1422 
1423     override def typeRef(implicit ctx: Context): TypeRef = {
1424       if (myTypeRef == null) myTypeRef = super.typeRef
1425       myTypeRef
1426     }
1427 
1428     override def appliedRef(implicit ctx: Context): Type = classInfo.appliedRef
1429 
1430     private def baseData(implicit onBehalf: BaseData, ctx: Context): (List[ClassSymbol], BaseClassSet) = {
1431       if (!baseDataCache.isValid) baseDataCache = BaseData.newCache()
1432       baseDataCache(this)
1433     }
1434 
1435     /** The base classes of this class in linearization order,
1436      *  with the class itself as first element.
1437      */
1438     def baseClasses(implicit onBehalf: BaseData, ctx: Context): List[ClassSymbol] =
1439       baseData._1
1440 
1441     /** A bitset that contains the superId's of all base classes */
1442     private def baseClassSet(implicit onBehalf: BaseData, ctx: Context): BaseClassSet =
1443       baseData._2
1444 
1445     def computeBaseData(implicit onBehalf: BaseData, ctx: Context): (List[ClassSymbol], BaseClassSet) = {
1446       def emptyParentsExpected =
1447         is(Package) || (symbol == defn.AnyClass) || ctx.erasedTypes && (symbol == defn.ObjectClass)
1448       if (classParents.isEmpty && !emptyParentsExpected)
1449         onBehalf.signalProvisional()
1450       val builder = new BaseDataBuilder
1451       for (p <- classParents) {
1452         if (p.typeSymbol.isClass) builder.addAll(p.typeSymbol.asClass.baseClasses)
1453         else assert(ctx.mode.is(Mode.Interactive), s"$this has non-class parent: $p")
1454         builder.addAll(p.typeSymbol.asClass.baseClasses)
1455       }
1456       (classSymbol :: builder.baseClasses, builder.baseClassSet)
1457     }
1458 
1459     final override def derivesFrom(base: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
1460       !isAbsent &&
1461       base.isClass &&
1462       (  (symbol eq base)
1463       || (baseClassSet contains base)
1464       || (this is Erroneous)
1465       || (base is Erroneous)
1466       )
1467 
1468     final override def isSubClass(base: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context) =
1469       derivesFrom(base) ||
1470         base.isClass && (
1471           (symbol eq defn.NothingClass) ||
1472             (symbol eq defn.NullClass) && (base ne defn.NothingClass))
1473 
1474     final override def typeParamCreationFlags = ClassTypeParamCreationFlags
1475 
1476     /** Hook to do a pre-enter test. Overridden in PackageDenotation */
1477     protected def proceedWithEnter(sym: Symbol, mscope: MutableScope)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = true
1478 
1479     /** Enter a symbol in current scope, and future scopes of same denotation.
1480      *  Note: We require that this does not happen after the first time
1481      *  someone does a findMember on a subclass.
1482      *  @param scope   The scope in which symbol should be entered.
1483      *                 If this is EmptyScope, the scope is `decls`.
1484      */
1485     def enter(sym: Symbol, scope: Scope = EmptyScope)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1486       val mscope = scope match {
1487         case scope: MutableScope =>
1488           // if enter gets a scope as an argument,
1489           // than this is a scope that will eventually become decls of this symbol.
1490           // And this should only happen if this is first time the scope of symbol
1491           // is computed, ie symbol yet has no future.
1492           assert(this.nextInRun.validFor.code <= this.validFor.code)
1493           scope
1494         case _ => unforcedDecls.openForMutations
1495       }
1496       if (proceedWithEnter(sym, mscope)) {
1497         enterNoReplace(sym, mscope)
1498         val nxt = this.nextInRun
1499         if (nxt.validFor.code > this.validFor.code) {
1500           this.nextInRun.asSymDenotation.asClass.enter(sym)
1501         }
1502         if (defn.isScalaShadowingPackageClass(sym.owner))
1503           defn.ScalaPackageClass.enter(sym)  // ScalaShadowing members are mirrored in ScalaPackage
1504       }
1505     }
1506 
1507     /** Enter a symbol in given `scope` without potentially replacing the old copy. */
1508     def enterNoReplace(sym: Symbol, scope: MutableScope)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1509       scope.enter(sym)
1510       if (myMemberCache != null) myMemberCache.invalidate(sym.name)
1511       if (!sym.flagsUNSAFE.is(Private)) invalidateMemberNamesCache()
1512     }
1513 
1514     /** Replace symbol `prev` (if defined in current class) by symbol `replacement`.
1515      *  If `prev` is not defined in current class, do nothing.
1516      *  @pre `prev` and `replacement` have the same name.
1517      */
1518     def replace(prev: Symbol, replacement: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1519       unforcedDecls.openForMutations.replace(prev, replacement)
1520       if (myMemberCache != null) myMemberCache.invalidate(replacement.name)
1521     }
1522 
1523     /** Delete symbol from current scope.
1524      *  Note: We require that this does not happen after the first time
1525      *  someone does a findMember on a subclass.
1526      */
1527     def delete(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
1528       info.decls.openForMutations.unlink(sym)
1529       if (myMemberCache != null) myMemberCache.invalidate(sym.name)
1530       if (!sym.flagsUNSAFE.is(Private)) invalidateMemberNamesCache()
1531     }
1532 
1533     /** Make sure the type parameters of this class appear in the order given
1534      *  by `typeParams` in the scope of the class. Reorder definitions in scope if necessary.
1535      */
1536     def ensureTypeParamsInCorrectOrder()(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1537       val tparams = typeParams
1538       if (!ctx.erasedTypes && !typeParamsFromDecls.corresponds(tparams)(_.name == _.name)) {
1539         val decls = info.decls
1540         val decls1 = newScope
1541         for (tparam <- typeParams) decls1.enter(decls.lookup(tparam.name))
1542         for (sym <- decls) if (!tparams.contains(sym)) decls1.enter(sym)
1543         info = classInfo.derivedClassInfo(decls = decls1)
1544         myTypeParams = null
1545       }
1546     }
1547 
1548     /** All members of this class that have the given name.
1549      *  The elements of the returned pre-denotation all
1550      *  have existing symbols.
1551      */
1552     final def membersNamed(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): PreDenotation = {
1553       val privates = info.decls.denotsNamed(name, selectPrivate)
1554       privates union nonPrivateMembersNamed(name).filterDisjoint(privates)
1555     }
1556 
1557     /** All non-private members of this class that have the given name.
1558      *  The elements of the returned pre-denotation all
1559      *  have existing symbols.
1560      *  @param inherited  The method is called on a parent class from computeNPMembersNamed
1561      */
1562     final def nonPrivateMembersNamed(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): PreDenotation = {
1563       Stats.record("nonPrivateMembersNamed")
1564       if (Config.cacheMembersNamed) {
1565         var denots: PreDenotation = memberCache lookup name
1566         if (denots == null) {
1567           denots = computeNPMembersNamed(name)
1568           memberCache.enter(name, denots)
1569         } else if (Config.checkCacheMembersNamed) {
1570           val denots1 = computeNPMembersNamed(name)
1571           assert(denots.exists == denots1.exists, s"cache inconsistency: cached: $denots, computed $denots1, name = $name, owner = $this")
1572         }
1573         denots
1574       } else computeNPMembersNamed(name)
1575     }
1576 
1577     private[core] def computeNPMembersNamed(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): PreDenotation = /*>|>*/ Stats.track("computeNPMembersNamed") /*<|<*/ {
1578       Stats.record("computeNPMembersNamed after fingerprint")
1579       ensureCompleted()
1580       val ownDenots = info.decls.denotsNamed(name, selectNonPrivate)
1581       if (debugTrace) // DEBUG
1582         println(s"$this.member($name), ownDenots = $ownDenots")
1583       def collect(denots: PreDenotation, parents: List[Type]): PreDenotation = parents match {
1584         case p :: ps =>
1585           val denots1 = collect(denots, ps)
1586           p.typeSymbol.denot match {
1587             case parentd: ClassDenotation =>
1588               denots1 union
1589                 parentd.nonPrivateMembersNamed(name)
1590                 .mapInherited(ownDenots, denots1, thisType)
1591             case _ =>
1592               denots1
1593           }
1594         case nil =>
1595           denots
1596       }
1597       if (name.isConstructorName) ownDenots
1598       else collect(ownDenots, classParents)
1599     }
1600 
1601     override final def findMember(name: Name, pre: Type, excluded: FlagSet)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = {
1602       val raw = if (excluded is Private) nonPrivateMembersNamed(name) else membersNamed(name)
1603       raw.filterExcluded(excluded).asSeenFrom(pre).toDenot(pre)
1604     }
1605 
1606     /** Compute tp.baseType(this) */
1607     final def baseTypeOf(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
1608 
1609       def foldGlb(bt: Type, ps: List[Type]): Type = ps match {
1610         case p :: ps1 => foldGlb(bt & baseTypeOf(p), ps1)
1611         case _ => bt
1612       }
1613 
1614       /** We cannot cache:
1615        *  - type variables which are uninstantiated or whose instances can
1616        *    change, depending on typerstate.
1617        *  - types where the underlying type is an ErasedValueType, because
1618        *    this underlying type will change after ElimErasedValueType,
1619        *    and this changes subtyping relations. As a shortcut, we do not
1620        *    cache ErasedValueType at all.
1621        */
1622       def isCachable(tp: Type, btrCache: BaseTypeMap): Boolean = {
1623         def inCache(tp: Type) = btrCache.containsKey(tp)
1624         tp match {
1625           case _: TypeErasure.ErasedValueType => false
1626           case tp: TypeRef if tp.symbol.isClass => true
1627           case tp: TypeVar => tp.inst.exists && inCache(tp.inst)
1628           //case tp: TypeProxy => inCache(tp.underlying) // disabled, can re-enable insyead of last two lines for performance testing
1629           //case tp: AndOrType => inCache(tp.tp1) && inCache(tp.tp2)
1630           case tp: TypeProxy => isCachable(tp.underlying, btrCache)
1631           case tp: AndOrType => isCachable(tp.tp1, btrCache) && isCachable(tp.tp2, btrCache)
1632           case _ => true
1633         }
1634       }
1635 
1636       def computeBaseTypeOf(tp: Type): Type = {
1637         if (Stats.monitored) {
1638           Stats.record("computeBaseType, total")
1639           Stats.record(s"computeBaseType, ${tp.getClass}")
1640         }
1641         if (symbol.isStatic && tp.derivesFrom(symbol) && symbol.typeParams.isEmpty)
1642           symbol.typeRef
1643         else tp match {
1644           case tp @ TypeRef(prefix, _) =>
1645             val subsym = tp.symbol
1646             if (subsym eq symbol) tp
1647             else subsym.denot match {
1648               case clsd: ClassDenotation =>
1649                 val owner = clsd.owner
1650                 val isOwnThis = prefix match {
1651                   case prefix: ThisType => prefix.cls eq owner
1652                   case NoPrefix => true
1653                   case _ => false
1654                 }
1655                 if (isOwnThis)
1656                   if (clsd.baseClassSet.contains(symbol)) foldGlb(NoType, clsd.classParents)
1657                   else NoType
1658                 else
1659                   baseTypeOf(clsd.typeRef).asSeenFrom(prefix, owner)
1660               case _ =>
1661                 baseTypeOf(tp.superType)
1662             }
1663           case tp @ AppliedType(tycon, args) =>
1664             val subsym = tycon.typeSymbol
1665             if (subsym eq symbol) tp
1666             else tycon.typeParams match {
1667               case LambdaParam(_, _) :: _ =>
1668                 baseTypeOf(tp.superType)
1669               case tparams: List[Symbol @unchecked] =>
1670                 baseTypeOf(tycon).subst(tparams, args)
1671             }
1672           case tp: TypeProxy =>
1673             baseTypeOf(tp.superType)
1674           case AndType(tp1, tp2) =>
1675             baseTypeOf(tp1) & baseTypeOf(tp2) match {
1676               case AndType(tp1a, tp2a) if (tp1a eq tp1) && (tp2a eq tp2) => tp
1677               case res => res
1678             }
1679           case OrType(tp1, tp2) =>
1680             baseTypeOf(tp1) | baseTypeOf(tp2) match {
1681               case OrType(tp1a, tp2a) if (tp1a eq tp1) && (tp2a eq tp2) => tp
1682               case res => res
1683             }
1684           case JavaArrayType(_) if symbol == defn.ObjectClass =>
1685             this.typeRef
1686           case _ =>
1687             NoType
1688         }
1689       }
1690 
1691       /*>|>*/ trace.onDebug(s"$tp.baseType($this)") /*<|<*/ {
1692         Stats.record("baseTypeOf")
1693         tp.stripTypeVar match {
1694           case tp: CachedType =>
1695           val btrCache = baseTypeCache
1696             try {
1697               var basetp = btrCache get tp
1698               if (basetp == null) {
1699                 btrCache.put(tp, NoPrefix)
1700                 basetp = computeBaseTypeOf(tp)
1701                 if (!basetp.exists) Stats.record("base type miss")
1702                 if (isCachable(tp, btrCache)) {
1703                   if (basetp.exists) Stats.record("cached base type hit")
1704                   else Stats.record("cached base type miss")
1705                   btrCache.put(tp, basetp)
1706                 }
1707                 else btrCache.remove(tp)
1708               } else if (basetp == NoPrefix)
1709                 throw CyclicReference(this)
1710               basetp
1711             }
1712             catch {
1713               case ex: Throwable =>
1714                 btrCache.put(tp, null)
1715                 throw ex
1716             }
1717           case tp =>
1718             computeBaseTypeOf(tp)
1719         }
1720       }
1721     }
1722 
1723     def memberNames(keepOnly: NameFilter)(implicit onBehalf: MemberNames, ctx: Context): Set[Name] =
1724      if ((this is PackageClass) || !Config.cacheMemberNames)
1725         computeMemberNames(keepOnly) // don't cache package member names; they might change
1726       else {
1727         if (!memberNamesCache.isValid) memberNamesCache = MemberNames.newCache()
1728         memberNamesCache(keepOnly, this)
1729       }
1730 
1731     def computeMemberNames(keepOnly: NameFilter)(implicit onBehalf: MemberNames, ctx: Context): Set[Name] = {
1732       var names = Set[Name]()
1733       def maybeAdd(name: Name) = if (keepOnly(thisType, name)) names += name
1734       for (p <- classParents)
1735         for (name <- p.typeSymbol.asClass.memberNames(keepOnly))
1736           maybeAdd(name)
1737       val ownSyms =
1738         if (keepOnly eq implicitFilter)
1739           if (this is Package) Iterator.empty
1740           else info.decls.iterator filter (_ is Implicit)
1741         else info.decls.iterator
1742       for (sym <- ownSyms) maybeAdd(sym.name)
1743       names
1744     }
1745 
1746     override final def fullNameSeparated(kind: QualifiedNameKind)(implicit ctx: Context): Name = {
1747       val cached = fullNameCache(kind)
1748       if (cached != null) cached
1749       else {
1750         val fn = super.fullNameSeparated(kind)
1751         fullNameCache = fullNameCache.updated(kind, fn)
1752         fn
1753       }
1754     }
1755 
1756     // to avoid overloading ambiguities
1757     override def fullName(implicit ctx: Context): Name = super.fullName
1758 
1759     override def primaryConstructor(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
1760       def constrNamed(cname: TermName) = info.decls.denotsNamed(cname).last.symbol
1761         // denotsNamed returns Symbols in reverse order of occurrence
1762       if (this.is(ImplClass)) constrNamed(nme.TRAIT_CONSTRUCTOR) // ignore normal constructor
1763       else if (this.is(Package)) NoSymbol
1764       else constrNamed(nme.CONSTRUCTOR).orElse(constrNamed(nme.TRAIT_CONSTRUCTOR))
1765     }
1766 
1767     /** The term parameter accessors of this class.
1768      *  Both getters and setters are returned in this list.
1769      */
1770     def paramAccessors(implicit ctx: Context): List[Symbol] =
1771       unforcedDecls.filter(_.is(ParamAccessor))
1772 
1773     /** If this class has the same `decls` scope reference in `phase` and
1774      *  `phase.next`, install a new denotation with a cloned scope in `phase.next`.
1775      */
1776     def ensureFreshScopeAfter(phase: DenotTransformer)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit =
1777       if (ctx.phaseId != phase.next.id) ensureFreshScopeAfter(phase)(ctx.withPhase(phase.next))
1778       else {
1779         val prevCtx = ctx.withPhase(phase)
1780         val prevClassInfo = current(prevCtx).asInstanceOf[ClassDenotation].classInfo(prevCtx)
1781         val ClassInfo(pre, _, ps, decls, selfInfo) = classInfo
1782         if (prevClassInfo.decls eq decls)
1783           copySymDenotation(info = ClassInfo(pre, classSymbol, ps, decls.cloneScope, selfInfo))
1784             .copyCaches(this, phase.next)
1785             .installAfter(phase)
1786       }
1787   }

1789   /** The denotation of a package class.
1790    *  It overrides ClassDenotation to take account of package objects when looking for members
1791    */
1792   final class PackageClassDenotation private[SymDenotations] (
1793     symbol: Symbol,
1794     ownerIfExists: Symbol,
1795     name: Name,
1796     initFlags: FlagSet,
1797     initInfo: Type,
1798     initPrivateWithin: Symbol,
1799     initRunId: RunId)
1800     extends ClassDenotation(symbol, ownerIfExists, name, initFlags, initInfo, initPrivateWithin, initRunId) {
1801 
1802     private[this] var packageObjCache: SymDenotation = _
1803     private[this] var packageObjRunId: RunId = NoRunId
1804 
1805     /** The package object in this class, of one exists */
1806     def packageObj(implicit ctx: Context): SymDenotation = {
1807       if (packageObjRunId != ctx.runId) {
1808         packageObjRunId = ctx.runId
1809         packageObjCache = NoDenotation // break cycle in case we are looking for package object itself
1810         packageObjCache = findMember(nme.PACKAGE, thisType, EmptyFlags).asSymDenotation
1811       }
1812       packageObjCache
1813     }
1814 
1815     /** Looks in both the package object and the package for members. The precise algorithm
1816      *  is as follows:
1817      *
1818      *  If this is the scala package look in the package first, and if nothing is found
1819      *  there, look in the package object second. Otherwise, look in the package object
1820      *  first, and if nothing is found there, in the package second.
1821      *
1822      *  The reason for the special treatment of the scala package is that if we
1823      *  complete it too early, we freeze its superclass Any, so that no members can
1824      *  be entered in it. As a consequence, there should be no entry in the scala package
1825      *  object that hides a class or object in the scala package of the same name, because
1826      *  the behavior would then be unintuitive for such members.
1827      */
1828     override def computeNPMembersNamed(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): PreDenotation =
1829       packageObj.moduleClass.denot match {
1830         case pcls: ClassDenotation if !pcls.isCompleting =>
1831           if (symbol eq defn.ScalaPackageClass) {
1832             val denots = super.computeNPMembersNamed(name)
1833             if (denots.exists) denots else pcls.computeNPMembersNamed(name)
1834           }
1835           else {
1836             val denots = pcls.computeNPMembersNamed(name)
1837             if (denots.exists) denots else super.computeNPMembersNamed(name)
1838           }
1839         case _ =>
1840           super.computeNPMembersNamed(name)
1841       }
1842 
1843     /** The union of the member names of the package and the package object */
1844     override def memberNames(keepOnly: NameFilter)(implicit onBehalf: MemberNames, ctx: Context): Set[Name] = {
1845       val ownNames = super.memberNames(keepOnly)
1846       packageObj.moduleClass.denot match {
1847         case pcls: ClassDenotation => ownNames union pcls.memberNames(keepOnly)
1848         case _ => ownNames
1849       }
1850     }
1851 
1852     /** If another symbol with the same name is entered, unlink it,
1853      *  and, if symbol is a package object, invalidate the packageObj cache.
1854      *  @return  `sym` is not already entered
1855      */
1856     override def proceedWithEnter(sym: Symbol, mscope: MutableScope)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = {
1857       val entry = mscope.lookupEntry(sym.name)
1858       if (entry != null) {
1859         if (entry.sym == sym) return false
1860         mscope.unlink(entry)
1861         if (sym.name == nme.PACKAGE) packageObjRunId = NoRunId
1862       }
1863       true
1864     }
1865 
1866     /** Unlink all package members defined in `file` in a previous run. */
1867     def unlinkFromFile(file: AbstractFile)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1868       val scope = unforcedDecls.openForMutations
1869       for (sym <- scope.toList.iterator) {
1870         // We need to be careful to not force the denotation of `sym` here,
1871         // otherwise it will be brought forward to the current run.
1872         if (sym.defRunId != ctx.runId && sym.isClass && sym.asClass.assocFile == file)
1873           scope.unlink(sym, sym.lastKnownDenotation.name)
1874       }
1875     }
1876   }

1879   extends SymDenotation(NoSymbol, NoSymbol, "<none>".toTermName, Permanent, NoType) {

1881     override def isTerm = false
1882     override def exists = false
1883     override def owner: Symbol = throw new AssertionError("NoDenotation.owner")
1884     override def computeAsSeenFrom(pre: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): SingleDenotation = this
1885     override def mapInfo(f: Type => Type)(implicit ctx: Context): SingleDenotation = this
1886     NoSymbol.denot = this

1892   /** Instances of LazyType are carried by uncompleted symbols.
1893    *  Note: LazyTypes double up as (constant) functions from Symbol and
1894    *  from (TermSymbol, ClassSymbol) to LazyType. That way lazy types can be
1895    *  directly passed to symbol creation methods in Symbols that demand instances
1896    *  of these function types.
1897    */
1898   abstract class LazyType extends UncachedGroundType
1899     with (Symbol => LazyType)
1900     with ((TermSymbol, ClassSymbol) => LazyType) { self =>
1901 
1902     /** Sets all missing fields of given denotation */
1903     def complete(denot: SymDenotation)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit
1904 
1905     def apply(sym: Symbol) = this
1906     def apply(module: TermSymbol, modcls: ClassSymbol) = this
1907 
1908     private[this] var myDecls: Scope = EmptyScope
1909     private[this] var mySourceModuleFn: Context => Symbol = NoSymbolFn
1910     private[this] var myModuleClassFn: Context => Symbol = NoSymbolFn
1911 
1912     /** A proxy to this lazy type that keeps the complete operation
1913      *  but provides fresh slots for scope/sourceModule/moduleClass
1914      */
1915     def proxy: LazyType = new LazyType {
1916       override def complete(denot: SymDenotation)(implicit ctx: Context) = self.complete(denot)
1917     }
1918 
1919     /** The type parameters computed by the completer before completion has finished */
1920     def completerTypeParams(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): List[TypeParamInfo] =
1921       if (sym is Touched) Nil // return `Nil` instead of throwing a cyclic reference
1922       else sym.info.typeParams
1923 
1924     def decls: Scope = myDecls
1925     def sourceModule(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = mySourceModuleFn(ctx)
1926     def moduleClass(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = myModuleClassFn(ctx)
1927 
1928     def withDecls(decls: Scope): this.type = { myDecls = decls; this }
1929     def withSourceModule(sourceModuleFn: Context => Symbol): this.type = { mySourceModuleFn = sourceModuleFn; this }
1930     def withModuleClass(moduleClassFn: Context => Symbol): this.type = { myModuleClassFn = moduleClassFn; this }
1931   }

1933   /** A subtrait of LazyTypes where completerTypeParams yields a List[TypeSymbol], which
1934    *  should be completed independently of the info.
1935    */
1936   trait TypeParamsCompleter extends LazyType {
1937     override def completerTypeParams(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): List[TypeSymbol] =
1938       unsupported("completerTypeParams") // should be abstract, but Scala-2 will then compute the wrong type for it
1939   }

1950   /** A lazy type for modules that points to the module class.
1951    *  Needed so that `moduleClass` works before completion.
1952    *  Completion of modules is always completion of the underlying
1953    *  module class, followed by copying the relevant fields to the module.
1954    */
1955   class ModuleCompleter(_moduleClass: ClassSymbol) extends LazyType {
1956     override def moduleClass(implicit ctx: Context) = _moduleClass
1957     def complete(denot: SymDenotation)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1958       val from = moduleClass.denot.asClass
1959       denot.setFlag(from.flags.toTermFlags & RetainedModuleValFlags)
1960       denot.annotations = from.annotations filter (_.appliesToModule)
1961         // !!! ^^^ needs to be revised later. The problem is that annotations might
1962         // only apply to the module but not to the module class. The right solution
1963         // is to have the module class completer set the annotations of both the
1964         // class and the module.
1965       denot.info = moduleClass.typeRef
1966       denot.privateWithin = from.privateWithin
1967     }
1968   }

1970   /** A completer for missing references */
1971   class StubInfo() extends LazyType {
1972 
1973     def initializeToDefaults(denot: SymDenotation, errMsg: => Message)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1974       denot.info = denot match {
1975         case denot: ClassDenotation =>
1976           ClassInfo(denot.owner.thisType, denot.classSymbol, Nil, EmptyScope)
1977         case _ =>
1978           ErrorType(errMsg)
1979       }
1980       denot.privateWithin = NoSymbol
1981     }
1982 
1983     def complete(denot: SymDenotation)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1984       val sym = denot.symbol
1985       def errMsg = BadSymbolicReference(denot)
1986       ctx.error(errMsg, sym.pos)
1987       if (ctx.debug) throw new scala.Error()
1988       initializeToDefaults(denot, errMsg)
1989     }
1990   }

2037   private abstract class InheritedCacheImpl(val createdAt: Period) extends InheritedCache {
2038     protected def sameGroup(p1: Phase, p2: Phase): Boolean
2039 
2040     private[this] var dependent: WeakHashMap[InheritedCache, Unit] = null
2041     private[this] var checkedPeriod: Period = Nowhere
2042 
2043     protected def invalidateDependents() = {
2044       if (dependent != null) {
2045         val it = dependent.keySet.iterator()
2046         while (it.hasNext()) it.next().invalidate()
2047       }
2048       dependent = null
2049     }
2050 
2051     protected def addDependent(dep: InheritedCache) = {
2052       if (dependent == null) dependent = new WeakHashMap
2053       dependent.put(dep, ())
2054     }
2055 
2056     def isValidAt(phase: Phase)(implicit ctx: Context) =
2057       checkedPeriod == ctx.period ||
2058         createdAt.runId == ctx.runId &&
2059         createdAt.phaseId < ctx.phases.length &&
2060         sameGroup(ctx.phases(createdAt.phaseId), phase) &&
2061         { checkedPeriod = ctx.period; true }
2062   }
2063 
2064   private class InvalidCache extends InheritedCache {
2065     def isValid(implicit ctx: Context) = false
2066     def isValidAt(phase: Phase)(implicit ctx: Context) = false
2067     def invalidate(): Unit = ()
2068   }
2069 
2070   private class MemberNamesImpl(createdAt: Period) extends InheritedCacheImpl(createdAt) with MemberNames {
2071     private[this] var cache: SimpleIdentityMap[NameFilter, Set[Name]] = SimpleIdentityMap.Empty
2072 
2073     final def isValid(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
2074       cache != null && isValidAt(ctx.phase)
2075 
2076     private[this] var locked = false
2077 
2078     /** Computing parent member names might force parents, which could invalidate
2079      *  the cache itself. In that case we should cancel invalidation and
2080      *  proceed as usual. However, all cache entries should be cleared.
2081      */
2082     def invalidate(): Unit =
2083       if (cache != null)
2084         if (locked) cache = SimpleIdentityMap.Empty
2085         else {
2086           cache = null
2087           invalidateDependents()
2088         }
2089 
2090     def apply(keepOnly: NameFilter, clsd: ClassDenotation)(implicit onBehalf: MemberNames, ctx: Context) = {
2091       assert(isValid)
2092       val cached = cache(keepOnly)
2093       try
2094         if (cached != null) cached
2095         else {
2096           locked = true
2097           val computed =
2098             try clsd.computeMemberNames(keepOnly)(this, ctx)
2099             finally locked = false
2100           cache = cache.updated(keepOnly, computed)
2101           computed
2102         }
2103       finally addDependent(onBehalf)
2104     }
2105 
2106     def sameGroup(p1: Phase, p2: Phase) = p1.sameMembersStartId == p2.sameMembersStartId
2107   }
2108 
2109   private class BaseDataImpl(createdAt: Period) extends InheritedCacheImpl(createdAt) with BaseData {
2110     private[this] var cache: (List[ClassSymbol], BaseClassSet) = null
2111 
2112     private[this] var valid = true
2113     private[this] var locked = false
2114     private[this] var provisional = false
2115 
2116     final def isValid(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = valid && isValidAt(ctx.phase)
2117 
2118     def invalidate(): Unit =
2119       if (valid && !locked) {
2120         cache = null
2121         valid = false
2122         invalidateDependents()
2123       }
2124 
2125     def signalProvisional() = provisional = true
2126 
2127     def apply(clsd: ClassDenotation)(implicit onBehalf: BaseData, ctx: Context)
2128         : (List[ClassSymbol], BaseClassSet) = {
2129       assert(isValid)
2130       try {
2131         if (cache != null) cache
2132         else {
2133           if (locked) throw CyclicReference(clsd)
2134           locked = true
2135           provisional = false
2136           val computed =
2137             try clsd.computeBaseData(this, ctx)
2138             finally locked = false
2139           if (!provisional) cache = computed
2140           else onBehalf.signalProvisional()
2141           computed
2142         }
2143       }
2144       finally addDependent(onBehalf)
2145     }
2146 
2147     def sameGroup(p1: Phase, p2: Phase) = p1.sameParentsStartId == p2.sameParentsStartId
2148   }

2150   class BaseClassSet(val classIds: Array[Int]) extends AnyVal {
2151     def contains(sym: Symbol, limit: Int) = {
2152       val id = sym.id
2153       var i = 0
2154       while (i < limit && classIds(i) != id) i += 1
2155       i < limit && {
2156         if (i > 0) {
2157           val t = classIds(i)
2158           classIds(i) = classIds(i - 1)
2159           classIds(i - 1) = t
2160         }
2161         true
2162       }
2163     }
2164     def contains(sym: Symbol): Boolean = contains(sym, classIds.length)
2165   }
2166 
2167   object BaseClassSet {
2168     def apply(bcs: List[ClassSymbol]): BaseClassSet =
2169       new BaseClassSet(bcs.toArray.map(_.id))
2170   }

2172   /** A class to combine base data from parent types */
2173   class BaseDataBuilder {
2174     private[this] var classes: List[ClassSymbol] = Nil
2175     private[this] var classIds = new Array[Int](32)
2176     private[this] var length = 0
2177 
2178     private def resize(size: Int) = {
2179       val classIds1 = new Array[Int](size)
2180       Array.copy(classIds, 0, classIds1, 0, classIds.length min size)
2181       classIds = classIds1
2182     }
2183 
2184     private def add(sym: Symbol): Unit = {
2185       if (length == classIds.length) resize(length * 2)
2186       classIds(length) = sym.id
2187       length += 1
2188     }
2189 
2190     def addAll(bcs: List[ClassSymbol]): this.type = {
2191       val len = length
2192       bcs match {
2193         case bc :: bcs1 =>
2194           addAll(bcs1)
2195           if (!new BaseClassSet(classIds).contains(bc, len)) {
2196             add(bc)
2197             classes = bc :: classes
2198           }
2199         case nil =>
2200       }
2201       this
2202     }
2203 
2204     def baseClassSet = {
2205       if (length != classIds.length) resize(length)
2206       new BaseClassSet(classIds)
2207     }
2208 
2209     def baseClasses: List[ClassSymbol] = classes
2210   }
